text: [SECTION] BASIC_INFO
Age: ~27 years
Location: Kanayannur, Kerala, India
Current role: AI / Machine Learning Engineer
Total experience: ~4–4.5 years in AI/ML
Education: B.Tech in Electronics & Communication (Kannur University), M.Tech in Signal Processing
[SECTION] PROFESSIONAL_GOALS
Grow as a strong AI/ML engineer with deeper fundamentals in algorithms and systems
Prepare for job change and technical interviews (DSA, system design, ML)
Reach advanced level in Data Structures & Algorithms from a near‑beginner starting point
Build a portfolio of solid coding, ML projects, and research/industry experience
Explore and potentially pursue international master’s programs in AI / Robotics (Europe, UK)
[SECTION] EDUCATION_AND_STUDY_ABROAD
Interested in MSc / Master’s programs focused on AI, ML, Robotics
Has compared universities like York and Aston (pros/cons, rankings, outcomes)
Actively looks for scholarships, assistantships, and funding options
Needs help with SOPs, motivation letters, and application positioning
[SECTION] TECH_STACK_AND_TOOLS
Primary language: Python
Comfortable with ML frameworks, scripting, virtual environments, and tooling
Heavy user of online coding and learning platforms (LeetCode, GeeksforGeeks, YouTube, Coursera, Udemy)
Uses GitHub for code and projects, and is open to using AI tools (like interview prep AIs)
[SECTION] DSA_AND_CODING_GOALS
Current self‑assessment: below beginner in DSA, wants systematic progression
Wants clear path from basics (arrays, strings, hashing, two pointers, recursion, trees, graphs, DP) to advanced topics
Plans to use LeetCode for structured practice and Codeforces for harder, contest‑style problems
Interested in Coursera DSA tracks such as “Algorithmic Toolbox” and “Data Structures and Algorithms Specialization”
Likes multi‑month roadmaps (e.g., months 0–2 fundamentals, 2–4 contests, etc.) with concrete problem targets
[SECTION] LEARNING_STYLE
Prefers concise but dense explanations with clear structure
Likes step‑by‑step roadmaps and checklists over vague advice
Comfortable with technical terminology but prefers practical examples and use‑cases
Uses videos (YouTube, courses), written notes, and coding practice side‑by‑side
Appreciates follow‑up problem sets or exact links/resources after a concept is explained
[SECTION] INTERVIEW_PREPARATION
Preparing for AI/ML roles and possibly product‑based software roles
Wants detailed technical + behavioral question banks tailored to experience
Uses or is open to using: Google Interview Warmup, Pramp, Interviewsby.ai, InterviewBit peer mocks, etc.
Values realistic mock interviews, feedback, and improvement plans
Needs help summarizing experience, explaining projects, and answering “tell me about yourself”‑type questions
[SECTION] DAILY_ROUTINE_AND_LIFESTYLE
Early riser: typically wakes around 4:00–4:30 AM
Morning routine includes exercise and getting ready for work
Engages in running, walking, and general fitness
Interested in skincare and wellness topics, occasionally seeks routines/product advice
Balances full‑time job, learning, and trading/investing
[SECTION] FINANCE_AND_TRADING
Active user of Upstox for equities and commodities, including silver on MCX
Has experience pledging holdings for margin and wants to understand risks and rules clearly
Interested in order types like stop‑loss, target, bracket/OCO, and GTT for risk control
Follows macro events like India’s Union Budget and how they affect sectors and pledged positions
Focuses on both short‑term trading decisions and long‑term wealth‑building strategies
[SECTION] PRODUCTIVITY_AND_HABITS
Values structured days, daily prioritization, and focusing on high‑impact work
Uses early mornings for deep work or learning whenever possible
Likes clear weekly/monthly plans for skills (DSA, ML, applications)
Open to systems like time‑boxing, outcome‑driven agendas, and habit tracking
[SECTION] PLATFORM_PREFERENCES
Learning: Coursera, Udemy, YouTube, GeeksforGeeks, NeetCode/Striver‑style playlists
Coding practice: LeetCode (primary), interested in Codeforces and possibly CodeChef
Trading: Upstox for stocks and MCX, follows Indian market news and sector updates
Communication: Works in English, wants to steadily improve spoken fluency and clarity
[SECTION] HOW_AI_AGENT_SHOULD_HELP
Generate concrete DSA roadmaps mapped to resources (courses + problem sets)
Suggest weekly plans that fit around full‑time work and early‑morning schedule
Provide tailored interview prep: questions, model answers, feedback templates, and mock interview structures
Support study‑abroad journey: university shortlists, SOP drafts, scholarship strategies
Explain trading and investing concepts clearly without giving direct stock tips
Always favor actionable, high‑signal advice over generic motivation
